{
  "texts": [
    "However, despite their advancements, LLMs are computationally expensive to run, making them less feasible for real-time moderation at scale (Kumar et al., 2024; Lai et al., 2022).",
    "In light of these limitations, our study investigates whether SLMs, which are more lightweight and cost-effective (Irugalbandara et al., 2024), can be fine-tuned to handle moderation tasks with comparable accuracy, potentially offering a balance between cost and effectiveness in online content moderation.",
    "We curate our data from the publicly available dataset of Reddit comment removals between May 10 th, 2016 and February 4 th, 2017 by Chandrasekharan et al. (2018) by sampling 10K comments (5K moderated and 5K unmoderated) for 15 popular subreddits from Reddit's landing page.",
    "For each subreddit, we split its data into 80/20 train/test sets.",
    "Appendix A includes the complete list, description, and subscriber statistics of the subreddits."
  ]
}